---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Pool Equipment Upgrades Gold Coast | Pumps, Heating, Chlorinator | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Pool equipment upgrades on the Gold Coast — variable-speed pumps (40-60% power saving), salt chlorinator, gas / heat-pump heating, LED, smart automation. QBCC-licensed.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://goldcoastpoolbuilders.com.au/services/equipment-upgrades/">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Pumps &middot; chlorination &middot; heating &middot; automation</span>
      <h1>Pool equipment upgrades across the <span class="accent">Gold Coast</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Old single-speed pumps cost $1,200&ndash;$2,000/yr to run. Old chlorinator
        cells run on year 8 and produce a fraction of their original output.
        Original solar heating systems from the 90s have failed and waste roof
        space. Modern variable-speed + smart-automation equipment saves
        40&ndash;60% of running cost and runs the pool quieter and cleaner.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free on-site quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Equipment categories &mdash; what to upgrade and why.</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">

        <h3>Variable-speed pump retrofit (the highest-ROI single change).</h3>
        <p>
          A 1990s&ndash;early-2010s pool pump is single-speed &mdash; runs flat-out
          whenever it&rsquo;s on. Power: 1.5kW. Annual cost on 8 hours/day filtration:
          ~$1,400&ndash;$1,800. Modern variable-speed pump (Astralpool Viron, Hayward
          MaxFlo VS, Pentair IntelliFlo): runs at 30&ndash;100% speed as needed,
          spends 80% of the time at <strong>~25% load</strong>. Same filtration,
          much quieter, <strong>40&ndash;60% lower power bill</strong>.
          Investment ~$1,800&ndash;$3,000 installed. Payback typically 18&ndash;30 months.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Salt chlorinator replacement.</h3>
        <p>
          Salt cells have a hard lifecycle &mdash; 4&ndash;7 years in Gold Coast
          conditions. Output drops linearly: a year-8 cell produces ~30% of its
          original chlorine, so you raise the dial and it consumes 3&times; the power
          to compensate. Replacement: cell-only ~$500&ndash;$900, full chlorinator
          unit (control + cell) ~$1,300&ndash;$2,500. Modern unit with timer +
          self-cleaning reverse polarity + smart-control extension: ~$2,200&ndash;$3,500.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Pool heating &mdash; gas vs electric heat pump vs solar.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Gas heater (Astralpool Hi-NRG, Hayward Universal):</strong> Fast heat-up, expensive to run. $3.5K&ndash;$6K installed. Running cost: $1,500&ndash;$3,500/yr depending on use.</li>
          <li><strong>Heat pump (Madimack Eco, Astralpool, Hayward HeatPro):</strong> Slow but cheap. $4.5K&ndash;$8K installed. Running cost: $500&ndash;$1,200/yr. Best value for most Gold Coast pools (year-round swim window).</li>
          <li><strong>Solar heating (panel system on roof):</strong> Free running cost, but Gold Coast winter sun isn&rsquo;t strong enough alone &mdash; needs gas or heat-pump backup. $3K&ndash;$6K install. Most owners now skip this and go pure heat-pump.</li>
          <li><strong>Hybrid (solar + heat pump):</strong> Solar in summer (free), heat-pump in winter. Premium spec. ~$10K combined.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">LED lighting retrofit.</h3>
        <p>
          Old halogen pool lights (300W incandescent) cost $40&ndash;$70/yr each to run
          and burn out every 12&ndash;18 months. Modern LED replacements
          (Astralpool, Hayward CrystaLogic, S.R. Smith) are 25&ndash;35W,
          last 15,000+ hours, and offer colour-change for under $200/yr in
          ambient lighting. Retrofit in existing niche: $300&ndash;$600 per light
          for plain white, $500&ndash;$900 for colour-change. 2&ndash;4 hours work.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Smart automation (Aquatic Plus, Astralpool Viron Connect, Hayward Omni).</h3>
        <p>
          Wi-Fi-connected controllers that let you start/stop pump and heating
          from your phone. Useful for: pre-heating pool for weekend swim,
          reducing pump-runtime in peak power tariff, monitoring chlorine and
          pH remotely, getting an alert if equipment fails. Investment
          $1,500&ndash;$3,500 retrofit on existing equipment. Mostly a
          lifestyle convenience, but the off-peak-tariff scheduling alone
          saves ~$300/yr.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Salt-environment equipment lifecycle &mdash; what to budget for.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Pump motor:</strong> 7&ndash;10 years coastal QLD (single-speed), 12&ndash;15 years (variable-speed, less heat stress)</li>
          <li><strong>Chlorinator cell:</strong> 4&ndash;7 years</li>
          <li><strong>Chlorinator control box:</strong> 10&ndash;15 years</li>
          <li><strong>Filter cartridge / media:</strong> 3&ndash;5 years (cartridge), 7&ndash;10 years (sand)</li>
          <li><strong>Heater:</strong> 8&ndash;12 years (gas), 10&ndash;15 years (heat pump)</li>
          <li><strong>Skimmer baskets, return jets, fittings:</strong> 8&ndash;15 years before plastic UV failure</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

